<br>
Sadly this is very true. I've often complained about the lack of decent mid level gear, the newbie caster gear in felwithe is much better than a lot of the stuff you can obtain in your 30's and 40's. Unfortuanately, unless VI were to implement the TLC, the majority of players would wait until spawns greened out, and then move in for the easy gear.<br>
<br>
This holds true at higher levels too, how many times have you seen people ask for strategies in the old school planes, only to see the initial response be: First, get a group of well geared level 60s, then..... <br>
<br>
Back to the point <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
New expansion content I'd like to see beyond the advertised features: <br>
<br>
- A Pet buff that allows a Slow Proc.<br>
<br>
- A pooper-scooper item that allows you to take horses indoors<br>
<br>
- Places for a magician to SOLO. Lets not leave the higher level casual gamers out of this expansion. I'd actually prefer to keep playing my mage to 65 if soloing remains a viable option. I shouldn't be forced to reroll a different character to still enjoy the game in a casual manner.<br>
<br>
- Once the expansion is released, I'd like to see the development team take a break from writing expansions and maybe try writing some new content for the legends server. We've been paying far too much for as little content as they've been providing lately. And don't get me started on the website.<br>
<br>
- Any kind of content that encourages people to play without the Trinity.<br>
<br>
<br>
EDIT: Good call on MSIV Raz. Only this time, make it so it actually summons a mob <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
